    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.29.6"/>
                <note type="curatorial">6</note>
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Jan. 7, 1961</dateline>
                </opener>
                
                <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                
                <p>I am so very sorry that I can't attend your birthday celebration tomorrow. I had hoped it would be possible, but as it isn't, I want to extend to you nevertheless my congratulations on your 80th birthday, and my best wishes for the future.</p>
                
                <p>You have been an inspiration to many of us since you camp to our campus.</p>
                
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>Elsa Nagel</signed>
                    
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><p>P.S. I have several times recommended your books to my german friends as
                    examples of good American literature.</p></postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
